---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How to Calculate Your Grade (Step-by-Step Guide)"
  description="Learn how to calculate your grade step-by-step. Includes formulas, examples, and a free grade calculator to check your work instantly."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>How to Calculate Your Grade (Step-by-Step)</h1>
    <p>
      Want to quickly figure out your grade? This guide shows you exactly how to calculate your average, 
      final grade, and what you need to pass — with simple steps and examples.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="card">

    <h2>📊 Method 1: Simple Grade Average</h2>
    <p>
      If all your assignments are worth the same amount, calculating your grade is easy.
    </p>

    <p><strong>Formula:</strong></p>
    <p>(Score₁ + Score₂ + Score₃ + …) ÷ Number of Assignments</p>

    <h3>Example:</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Assignment 1: 90%</li>
      <li>Assignment 2: 80%</li>
      <li>Assignment 3: 85%</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      (90 + 80 + 85) ÷ 3 = <strong>85%</strong>
    </p>

    <p>
      👉 Want to skip the math? Try our 
      <a href="/grade-calculator">Grade Calculator</a>.
    </p>

  </div>

  <div class="card">

    <h2>⚖️ Method 2: Weighted Grade Calculation</h2>
    <p>
      Many classes use weighted categories like homework, tests, and quizzes.
    </p>

    <h3>Example:</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Homework = 30%</li>
      <li>Tests = 50%</li>
      <li>Quizzes = 20%</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      Multiply each category by its weight:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>Homework: 90 × 0.30 = 27</li>
      <li>Tests: 80 × 0.50 = 40</li>
      <li>Quizzes: 85 × 0.20 = 17</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      Total = <strong>84%</strong>
    </p>

    <p>
      👉 Use the 
      <a href="/weighted-grade-calculator">Weighted Grade Calculator</a> 
      to do this instantly.
    </p>

  </div>

  <div class="card">

    <h2>🎯 Method 3: What Grade Do I Need?</h2>
    <p>
      Trying to figure out what you need on your final exam to pass?
    </p>

    <p>
      You need:
    </p>

    <p><strong>(Desired Grade − Current Grade Contribution) ÷ Final Weight</strong></p>

    <p>
      👉 Skip the formula and use the 
      <a href="/what-grade-do-i-need-calculator">What Grade Do I Need Calculator</a>.
    </p>

  </div>

  <div class="card">

    <h2>🎓 How to Calculate GPA</h2>
    <p>
      GPA is calculated by converting letter grades into points.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>A = 4.0</li>
      <li>B = 3.0</li>
      <li>C = 2.0</li>
      <li>D = 1.0</li>
      <li>F = 0.0</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      Add your points and divide by the number of classes.
    </p>

    <p>
      👉 Use our 
      <a href="/gpa-calculator">GPA Calculator</a> 
      to calculate it instantly.
    </p>

  </div>

  <div class="card">

    <h2>🚀 Final Tip</h2>
    <p>
      Calculating grades manually is helpful, but using tools saves time and avoids mistakes.
    </p>

    <p>
      Explore all tools:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><a href="/grade-calculator">Grade Calculator</a></li>
      <li><a href="/final-exam-calculator">Final Exam Calculator</a></li>
      <li><a href="/weighted-grade-calculator">Weighted Grade Calculator</a></li>
      <li><a href="/gpa-calculator">GPA Calculator</a></li>
      <li><a href="/what-grade-do-i-need-calculator">What Grade Do I Need Calculator</a></li>
    </ul>

  </div>

</BaseLayout>